2.  Length‐2 spans:

   (1–2): Combine {5,8,19,36,40,75} × {17,36,57,63,65,68,78}.  
     Only rule 57→75 65 applies ⇒ cell[1,2]={NT57}.  

   (2–3): Combine {17,36,57,63,65,68,78} × {9,18,26,36}.  
     Only rule 15→68 18 applies ⇒ cell[2,2]={NT15}.  

   (3–4): Combine {9,18,26,36} × {1,10,12,15,42,71,76}.  
     No binary rule matches ⇒ cell[3,2]=∅.

Because the span (3–4) never fills, no higher‐level cell can ever produce S, so the grammar cannot generate “t20 t19 t8 t0.”
